## When to use
When you need to inspect and understand detailed information about your system's disk I/O performance over time.

## Approach
Use the `shell_exec` tool with the `iostat` command. Common advanced options include `-d` for displaying only disk statistics, `-x` for extended statistical details, and `-t` for timestamped output. For continuous monitoring of disk I/O statistics, you can use `iostat -dx 1`.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "iostat -dx 1"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run an `iostat` command that monitors detailed disk usage every second with extended statistics and timestamps.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure that the system has installed and configured the necessary utilities for running shell commands.
- Be aware of the interval duration when using continuous monitoring as it can generate a large amount of output quickly.